  "doc_id": "58993",
  "text": "Luteal endothelial cells (LECs) culture. LECs were used in the present study using the method described by SpanelBorowski et al. [CITATION_1] . Cytokeratin-negative LECs isolated from the CLs of the cows during the mid-luteal phase were used as described previously [CITATION_2] . LECs were grown on plates pre-coated with 1% Vitrogen in DMEM/F-12 medium containing 5% FBS, 2.2% NaHCO3, gentamicin solution, and amphotericin B solution. All experiments in the present study were carried out on LECs from passages 5 to 8.",
